20waterfall%20exploring%20in%20Oregon%2C%20and%20leaf%20peeping%20in%20Canada.%20They%20saw%20moose%20and%20orcas%20in%20Alaska%2C%20manatees%20in%20the%20Dominican%20Republic%2C%20and%20sheep%20in%20the%20Irish%20countryside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20also%20volunteer%20at%20a%20local%20food%20bank%20each%20month%2C%20go%20to%20comedy%20shows%20at%20Mall%20of%20America%2C%20routinely%20go%20to%20concerts%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20Johnson%20nor%20her%20husband%20grew%20up%20wealthy%2C%20and%20the%20couple%20never%20expected%20to%20have%20such%20an%20indulgent%20lifestyle.%20Johnson's%20husband%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20faced%20%26quot%3Ba%20very%20bleak%20outlook%26quot%3B%20for%20his%20career%20when%20he%20graduated%20from%20college%20in%202008%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20Great%20Recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20now%2C%2016%20years%20later%2C%20the%2030-something%20couple%20make%20a%20generous%20joint%20income%20of%20just%20under%20%24300%2C000.%20That%20income%2C%20their%20hard%20work%2C%20and%20a%20dash%20of%20savvy%20investing%20are%20largely%20responsible%20for%20the%20lifestyle%20they%20lead%20%E2%80%94%20but%20there's%20another%20big%20factor.%20The%20Johnsons%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-typical-dink-double-income-no-kid-net-worth-retirement-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EDINKS%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20dual-income%20couple%20with%20no%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20costs%20of%20rearing%20a%20child%20have%20skyrocketed%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20especially%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-gen-z-parents-struggle-lonely-childcare-costs-money-friends-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eparents%20get%20less%20help%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20their%20families%20and%20communities.%20Raising%20a%20kid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-costs-raise-kid-us-americans-have-fewer-kids-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecould%20cost%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20parents%20upward%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-kids-cost-raising-child-inflation-childcare-tax-exemptions-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%2426%2C000%20this%20year%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Being%20a%20DINK%20has%20always%20been%20a%20way%20to%20save%20money%2C%20but%20as%20the%20stigma%20around%20the%20choice%20to%20be%20child-free%20has%20faded%2C%20more%20and%20more%20Americans%20see%20being%20a%20DINK%20as%20the%20key%20to%20a%20new%20American%20dream%20of%20financial%20stability%2C%20freedom%20of%20choice%2C%20and%20a%20comfortable%20retirement.%20DINKs%20are%20proudly%20emerging%20as%20an%20aspirational%20class%20for%20young%20people%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they're%20ready%20to%20live%20it%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ELifestyles%20of%20the%20DINKs%20and%20the%20child-free%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EJohnson's%20Tinder%20profile%20set%20her%20on%20her%20path%20to%20DINKhood.%20In%20early%20adulthood%2C%20she%20never%20felt%20the%20desire%20to%20have%20children%20but%20wanted%20to%20keep%20an%20open%20mind.%20As%20the%20years%20went%20on%2C%20even%20as%20she%20saw%20her%20peers%20having%20kids%2C%20she%20said%20her%20%26quot%3Bbeliefs%20just%20never%20changed%20and%20completely%20solidified.%26quot%3B%20So%20when%20she%20set%20up%20her%20dating%20profile%2C%20Johnson%20included%20in%20her%20bio%20that%20she%20didn't%20want%20to%20have%20kids%20of%20her%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20wanted%20to%20weed%20out%20the%20ones%20I%20wouldn't%20be%20compatible%20with%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20It%20worked.%20Johnson%20recalled%20that%20on%20their%20second%20or%20third%20date%2C%20she%20and%20her%20now-husband%20discussed%20the%20topic%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20were%20on%20the%20same%20page.%20The%20pair%20married%20in%202022%2C%20and%20Johnson%20said%20their%20decision%20to%20live%20as%20DINKs%20had%20been%20enriching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20makes%20my%20life%20more%20meaningful%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20occupational%20therapist%20said%20of%20her%20choice%20to%20be%20child-free.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20I%20can%20give%20more%20to%20my%20patients%20at%20work.%20I%20have%20more%20time%20to%20see%20my%20loved%20ones%20and%20family.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20emotional%20value%20Johnson%20ascribes%20to%20her%20DINK%20status%2C%20there%20are%20the%20dollars-and-cents%20benefits%20to%20the%20lifestyle.%20Her%20husband%2C%20who%20works%20in%20banking%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20very%20big%20spreadsheet%20guy%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnson%20said%2C%20and%20the%20couple%20track%20their%20finances%20%26quot%3Breligiously.%26quot%3B%20Part%20of%20that%20maniacal%20focus%20is%20tracking%20their%20net%20worth.%20The%20latest%20tally%3F%20About%20%241.1%20million%2C%20a%20combination%20of%20the%20equity%20they've%20been%20able%20to%20accumulate%20in%20their%20new-build%2C%20suburban%20Minneapolis%20townhome%20and%20their%20retirement%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20occupational%20therapist%20who%20works%20with%20older%20people%2C%20Johnson%20said%2C%20she%20sees%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20biggest%20downsides%20to%20being%20a%20DINK%20is%20not%20having%20your%20children%20there%20to%20support%20you%20and%20help%20you%20age%20in%20place%20as%20you%20get%20older.%26quot%3B%20So%20in%20addition%20to%20enjoying%20travel%20now%2C%20it's%20important%20for%20the%20couple%20to%20have%20%26quot%3Bthe%20financial%20resources%20in%20place%20to%20support%20safe%20living%20when%20we're%20old%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20adults%2C%20having%20children%20holds%20a%20massive%20amount%20of%20intrinsic%20value%2C%20but%20there's%20no%20denying%20that%20those%20who%20choose%20to%20forgo%20parenthood%20gain%20a%20serious%20financial%20edge.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20net-worth%20data%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20most%20recent%20Survey%20of%20Consumer%20Finances%20showed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnet-worth-dink-child-free-couples-win-the-economy-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethere's%20never%20been%20a%20better%20time%20to%20be%20a%20DINK%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Child-free%20couples'%20median%20net%20worth%20of%20%24399%2C000%20in%202022%20was%20the%20highest%20of%20all%20types%20of%20family%20structures%20studied%20by%20the%20survey%20and%20almost%20%24150%2C000%20more%20than%20couples%20with%20kids.%20The%20median%20net%20worth%20of%20DINKs%20was%20also%20more%20than%20%24100%2C000%20higher%20than%20it%20was%20in%202019%2C%20and%20the%20gap%20between%20child-free%20couples%20and%20couples%20with%20kids%20has%20only%20widened%20as%20prices%20on%20items%20and%20services%20parents%20need%20most%2C%20such%20as%20childcare%20and%20food%2C%20have%20spiked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FmyyVQ%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Net%20worth%20by%20family%20structure%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAmy%20Blackstone%2C%20the%20author%20of%20the%202019%20book%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.penguinrandomhouse.com%2Fbooks%2F592243%2Fchildfree-by-choice-by-dr-amy-blackstone%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EChildfree%20by%20Choice%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20that%20the%20financial%20gap%20between%20DINKs%20and%20couples%20with%20kids%20wasn't%20solely%20because%20of%20the%20choice%20about%20children.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20it's%20also%20a%20bit%20of%20selection%20bias.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20people%20who%20already%20have%20higher%20incomes%2C%20higher%20education%2C%20and%20are%20generally%20more%20privileged%20who%20opt%20out%20of%20parenthood%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20DINKs%20like%20the%20Johnsons%20demonstrate%20that%20as%20the%20American%20dream%20of%20homeownership%20and%20putting%20kids%20through%20college%20gets%20further%20out%20of%20reach%2C%20forgoing%20children%20is%20one%20way%20to%20achieve%20the%20upward%20economic%20mobility%20that%20many%20parents%20find%20more%20difficult%20to%20reach.%20Child-free%20couples%20have%20more%20free%20cash%20flow%20that%20can%20be%20invested%20in%20real%20estate%20or%20stocks.%20And%20while%20the%20pandemic's%20fiscal%20stimulus%20left%20pretty%20much%20everyone%20with%20more%20cash%2C%20DINKs%20seemed%20to%20emerge%20victorious%20in%20the%20battle%20to%20grow%20wealth.%20After%20a%20few%20years%20of%20saving%2C%20the%20Johnsons%20are%20free%20of%20student%20debt%20and%20said%20they're%20in%20a%20financial%20position%20to%20start%20planning%20for%20an%20early%20retirement%20in%20their%2050s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20from%20a%20middle-class%20family%2C%20and%20my%20husband%20from%20a%20lower-class%20upbringing%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnson%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20experienced%20paycheck-to-paycheck%20living%2C%20started%20his%20first%20job%20at%20age%2011%20delivering%20newspapers.%20We%20feel%20very%20fortunate%20for%20our%20current%20economic%20stability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20not%20all%20DINKs%20are%20raking%20in%20six-figure%20incomes%20and%20investing%20in%20real%20estate.%20Alex%20Killingsworth%20is%20a%2025-year-old%20entrepreneur%20building%20a%20content-writing%20business%2C%20and%20his%20wife%20is%20a%20full-time%20graduate%20student.%20She%20makes%20%2414%2C000%20a%20year%20as%20a%20teaching%20assistant%2C%20while%20his%20business%20earned%20them%20%2484%2C000%20in%202023.%20Not%20having%20kids%20has%20allowed%20them%20to%20invest%20in%20his%20startup%20and%20her%20higher%20education%2C%20both%20of%20which%20they%20believe%20will%20pay%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20'investing'%20in%20the%20work%20I'm%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20Killingsworth%20said.%20%26quot%3BLikewise%20for%20my%20wife%2C%20almost%20all%20of%20her%20income%20is%20going%20into%20research%2C%20so%20our%20actual%20take-home%20pay%20is%20quite%20a%20bit%20lower.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20they%20had%20kids%2C%20paying%20the%20bills%20could%20be%20tougher%20for%20them.%20Instead%2C%20they're%20buying%20wine%20and%20whiskey%2C%20maxing%20out%20a%20retirement%20account%2C%20and%20taking%20advantage%20of%20the%20freedom%20to%20spend%20Thanksgiving%20in%20Alaska%2C%20visit%20family%20in%20Texas%2C%20or%20go%20to%20Broadway%20shows%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20if%20we%20have%20any%20hacks%20or%20tricks%20here%2C%20but%20I%20have%20been%20told%20all%20of%20the%20extra%20income%20has%20a%20tendency%20to%20dry%20up%20when%20you%20have%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20Killingsworth%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20if%20that's%20true%2C%20but%20it's%20better%20to%20overprepare%20than%20under%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGrowing%20acceptance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20financial%20upsides%20of%20being%20a%20DINK%20used%20to%20come%20with%20a%20cost%3A%20In%201974%2C%20a%20substitute%20teacher%20named%20Marcia%20Drut-Davis%20was%20fired%20from%20her%20job%20and%20received%20death%20threats%20after%20discussing%20her%20choice%20to%20be%20child-free%20on%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B60%20Minutes%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EWhen%20another%20school%20asked%20her%20to%20give%20a%20speech%20on%20her%20decision%2C%20angry%20parents%20carrying%20signs%20calling%20her%20%26quot%3Bthe%20devil's%20sister%26quot%3B%20crowded%20the%20entrance%2C%20and%20the%20teacher%20who%20provided%20closing%20remarks%20after%20the%20speech%20denounced%20her%20in%20front%20of%20the%20auditorium.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%202013%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BConfessions%20of%20a%20Childfree%20Woman%2C%26quot%3B%20Drut-Davis%20recalls%20the%20teacher%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BHow%20will%20you%20feel%20when%20you're%20old%20and%20alone%20with%20no%20one%20to%20take%20care%20of%20you%3F%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EHow%20will%20you%20feel%20without%20a%20grandchild%20to%20give%20you%20chocolate%20kisses%3F%20You're%20a%20sad%20excuse%20for%20a%20woman.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20the%20social%20stigma%20around%20choosing%20not%20to%20have%20children%20has%20been%20substantial%2C%20but%20Blackstone%20said%20that%20she'd%20noticed%20a%20major%20shift%20in%20acceptance%20since%20she%20began%20research%20for%20her%20book%20in%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20say%20that%20it's%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Z%20who%20have%20really%20done%20the%20heavy%20lifting%20in%20terms%20of%20bringing%20this%20conversation%20out%20into%20the%20open%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20to%20say%20Gen%20X%20didn't%20contribute%20to%20the%20conversation%20%E2%80%94%20Blackstone%20is%20a%20child-free%20Xer%20%E2%80%94%20but%20she%20said%20the%20younger%20generations'%20experiences%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-money-financial-economic-trauma-recession-student-debt-inflation-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E2008%20financial%20crisis%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-z-no-point-saving-climate-change-inflation-homeownership-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eaccelerated%20climate%20crisis%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20increasingly%20divisive%20politics%20made%20the%20choice%20to%20forgo%20kids%20more%20acceptable%20to%20a%20wider%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3De3a4ee20460e599af773acd0b26ee1983766d8f9996fe47da8991f2db80d470b%26postID%3D65a7f880a62cdd3ed804e0fa%26postSlug%3Dparents-dinks-winning-childfree-economy-finances-income-vacation-retirement-kids-2024-2%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%25