ps%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6570faea58e7c0c29a2a79f5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224642%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEthan%20Evans%20writes%20that%20if%20you%20get%20the%20sense%20that%20a%20layoff%20is%20coming%2C%20you%20want%20to%20try%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20that%20process%20so%20you%20can%20influence%20the%20outcome.%3Cp%3ECreative_Outlet%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EEthan%20Evans%20is%20a%20retired%20Amazon%20VP%20who%20invented%20products%20like%20Prime%20Video%20and%20Prime%20Gaming.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEvans%20says%20he%20once%20conducted%20layoffs%20at%20a%20startup%2C%20and%20then%20was%20laid%20off%20himself.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20gives%20a%204-part%20framework%20on%20how%20to%20successfully%20(and%20humanely)%20oversee%20layoffs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20once%20laid%20off%20one-third%20of%20the%20startup%20I%20had%20just%20helped%20to%20build.%20I%20was%20the%20Vice%20President%20of%20Operations%20and%20owned%20a%20range%20of%20functions%2C%20including%20human%20resources%20and%20recruiting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flate-stage-startups-vc-lack-funding-forced-shut-down-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshrinking%20startup%3C%2Fa%3E%20no%20longer%20needs%20to%20recruit%2C%20I%20administered%20the%20layoff%20as%20my%20last%20act%20and%20was%20laid%20off%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20the%20next%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20entire%20year%20beforehand%2C%20I%20had%20been%20focused%20on%20hiring%20like%20crazy.%20The%20internet%20wisdom%20of%20the%20day%20was%20%26quot%3Bget%20big%20fast%2C%26quot%3B%20so%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-partners-gather-in-miami-to-plan-banks-future-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoldman%20Sachs%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20given%20us%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20and%20told%20us%20to%20grow%20as%20fast%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20year%2C%20we%20went%20from%2050%20employees%20to%20150.%20Four%20months%20and%20two%20waves%20of%20layoffs%20later%2C%20we%20were%20back%20at%2050.%20We%20were%20following%20%26quot%3Bexpert%26quot%3B%20advice%20and%20ended%20up%20following%20it%20off%20a%20cliff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20we%20are%20seeing%20tons%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-sweeping-us-these-are-companies-making-cuts-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elayoffs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20good%20leaders%20need%20to%20be%20skilled%20at%20all%20parts%20of%20the%20layoff%20process%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20their%20team%20members%20and%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20several%20parts%20to%20handling%20this%20process%20well%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Planning%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20your%20level%20in%20the%20company%2C%20you%20may%20be%20part%20of%20planning%20the%20layoff%20and%20choosing%20who%20will%20stay%20and%20who%20will%20go.%20If%20you%20get%20the%20sense%20that%20a%20layoff%20is%20coming%2C%20you%20want%20to%20try%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20that%20process%20so%20you%20can%20influence%20the%20outcome.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EBeing%20part%20of%20these%20decisions%20is%20gut-wrenching%20because%20you're%20making%20choices%20that%20impact%20your%20employees%20and%20their%20families.%20However%2C%20it's%20even%20worse%20to%20find%20yourself%20as%20%26quot%3Bjust%20the%20messenger.%26quot%3B%20That%20conveys%20bad%20news%20and%20helplessness%20all%20at%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Communication%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20individual%20reacts%20to%20a%20layoff%20in%20very%20different%20ways.%20I%20once%20had%20an%20employee%20who%20went%20back%20to%20his%20desk%20and%20shattered%20a%20glass%20award%20the%20company%20had%20given%20him%2C%20feeling%20it%20was%20meaningless%20now%20that%20he%20had%20been%20laid%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20employees%20have%20become%20so%20upset%20that%20they%20could%20not%20complete%20the%20meetings.%20We%20had%20to%20let%20them%20go%20home%2C%20process%20the%20event%2C%20and%20come%20back%20the%20next%20day%20to%20finish%20the%20conversation.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20key%20as%20a%20leader%20in%20any%20of%20these%20circumstances%20is%20to%20be%20calm%20yourself%20so%20that%20you%20can%20adapt%20to%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20employee%20and%20the%20situation.%20Don't%20feel%20that%20you%20must%20force%20the%20employee%20through%20a%20script%20if%20it%20is%20the%20wrong%20thing%20for%20the%20human%20being%20across%20the%20table.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhile%20you%20may%20have%20information%20that%20you%20must%20convey%20for%20legal%20reasons%2C%20if%20the%20employee%20cannot%20handle%20it%2C%20take%20a%20break.%20Let%20them%20have%20a%20minute%2C%20or%20consider%20coming%20back%20the%20next%20day%20to%20get%20the%20details.%20Scripts%20are%20great%20to%20help%20you%20be%20organized%2C%20avoid%20omissions%2C%20and%20control%20your%20own%20emotions%2C%20but%20you%20should%20flex%20your%20delivery%20based%20on%20the%20situation.%20Behave%20as%20you%20would%20want%20your%20leader%20to%20behave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Helping%20impacted%20employees%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20draining%20as%20the%20actual%20layoff%20can%20be%2C%20the%20real%20work%20of%20a%20leader%20begins%20after%20the%20list%20is%20made.%20This%20is%20where%20you%20begin%20supporting%20them%20in%20finding%20their%20next%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20often%20possible%20to%20place%20team%20members%20into%20other%20open%20roles%20in%20your%20company%2C%20either%20directly%20or%20by%20strongly%20recommending%20them%20to%20leaders%20who%20are%20still%20hiring.%20Other%20times%2C%20you%20can%20be%20helpful%20by%20making%20referrals%20and%20introductions%20to%20leaders%20in%20other%20organizations.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIn%20my%20case%2C%20I%20organized%20a%20meetup%20of%20laid-off%20employees%20and%20gave%20them%20all%20a%20copy%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D7f225184d39fb864ca1439191b2950f5826c8804e0f6cad337d030455a3ede0d%26postID%3D65c295e9ee61557013f9de2d%26postSlug%3Dhow-to-handle-layoffs-retired-amazon-vp-explains-2024-2%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FWhat-Color-Your-Parachute-Meaningful%252Fdp%252F1984861204%252F%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhat%20Color%20Is%20Your%20Parachute%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20job-hunting%20manual.%20We%20sat%20together%2C%20discussed%20job%20search%20tips%2C%20and%20created%20a%20process%20to%20share%20leads%20with%20one%20another.%20This%20collaborative%20process%20gave%20the%20affected%20employees%20a%20support%20network%20and%20additional%20resources%20to%20make%20their%20next%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Retaining%20your%20team%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20remain%20at%20the%20company%20yourself%2C%20your%20other%20challenge%20as%20a%20leader%20is%20retaining%20and%20motivating%20your%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20wave%20of%20layoffs%2C%20the%20team%20will%20have%20many%20feelings%20and%20concerns.%20These%20will%20include%20grief%20and%20anger%20about%20departing%20colleagues%2C%20feelings%20that%20the%20company%20has%20failed%20them%2C%20worries%20about%20their%20own%20jobs%2C%20and%20concern%20about%20how%20to%20handle%20the%20newly%20unowned%20work.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThese%20concerns%20all%20have%20emotional%20roots.%20Too%20often%2C%20particularly%20at%20tech%20companies%2C%20we%20focus%20on%20logical%20explanations%20when%20the%20employees%20(human%20beings!)%20actually%20need%20help%20with%20their%20worries.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EGive%20them%20time%2C%20space%2C%20and%20support%20in%20adjusting%20to%20the%20new%20circumstances.%20Then%2C%20lay%20out%20a%20clear%20path%20forward.%20Most%20employees%20can%20and%20will%20re-engage%20after%20a%20layoff%20if%20you%20can%20help%20them%20see%20how%20they%20and%20the%20company%20can%20succeed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20need%20skilled%2C%20compassionate%2C%20and%20prepared%20leaders%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20one%20gets%20training%20in%20how%20to%20handle%20a%20layoff%20because%20it%20is%20a%20taboo%20subject%20that%20companies%20avoid.%20But%2C%20in%20order%20to%20protect%20yourself%20and%20your%20team%2C%20you%20have%20to%20educate%20yourself%20in%20advance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20long-term%20leaders%20will%20go%20through%20several%20cycles%20of%20layoffs%20in%20their%20careers%2C%20and%20the%20best%20leaders%20recognize%20that%20layoffs%20are%20relatively%20common.%20Knowing%20this%2C%20they%20prepare%20themselves%20to%20lead%20well%20through%20layoffs%20instead%20of%20being%20caught%20off%20guard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20made%20the%20call%20to%20lay%20off%20employees%2C%20and%20I%20have%20been%20laid%20off%20myself.%20Reflecting%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20experience%20I%20can%20say%20without%20a%20doubt%20that%20a%20skilled%2C%20compassionate%2C%20and%20prepared%20leader%20makes%20all%20the%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEthan%20Evans%20is%20a%20retired%20Amazon%20vice%20president%20with%20over%2023%20years%20of%20experience%20as%20a%20business%20executive.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-handle-layoffs-retired-amazon-vp-explains-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707300721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c29e836fcb546d2d4ccb93%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-handle-layoffs-retired-amazon-vp-explains-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20laying%20off%20a%20third%20of%20a%20startup%20he%20helped%20build%2C%20Ethan%20Evans%20was%20laid%20off%20the%20next%20day.%20He%20learned%20there%20are%20several%20parts%20to%20conducting%20layoffs%20well.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Ethan%20E