%5C%221920%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BUnmasking%20AI%26quot%3B%20by%20Joy%20Buolamwini.%3Cp%3ECover%20art%20by%20Malika%20Favre%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBusiness%20Insider%20reviewed%20%26quot%3BUnmasking%20AI%3A%20My%20Mission%20to%20Protect%20What%20Is%20Human%20in%20a%20World%20of%20Machines.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJoy%20Buolamwini%2C%20the%20author%2C%20discussed%20her%20inspiration%20and%20context%20for%20the%20book%20with%20BI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EReaders%20come%20away%20understanding%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20how%20it%20can%20perpetuate%20bias%2C%20and%20what%20we%20can%20do%20about%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-ai-100-2023-the-people-who-make-ai-intelligent-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EJoy%20Buolamwini%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E's%20debut%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BUnmasking%20AI%3A%20My%20Mission%20to%20Protect%20What%20Is%20Human%20in%20a%20World%20of%20Machines%2C%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20a%20triumph%20in%20a%20literary%20work%20about%20artificial%20intelligence%20that%20isn't%20boring%2C%20highfalutin%2C%20or%20dry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuolamwini's%20autobiographical%20work%20offers%20an%20origin%20story%20of%20AI%20technology%20as%20well%20as%20an%20account%20of%20the%20author's%20path.%20Its%20striking%20accessibility%20mirrors%20the%20meteoric%20rise%20of%20AI%20into%20the%20mainstream.%20The%20Massachusetts%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20researcher%20flexes%20her%20prose%20and%20occasionally%20documents%20her%20journey%20in%20an%20almost%20scientific%20telling%20of%20her%20early%20life%20in%20rural%20Mississippi%20with%20Ghanaian%20Canadian%20parents%20who%20encouraged%20her%20intellectual%20curiosity.%20Buolamwini%20would%20later%20go%20on%20to%20advise%20Congress%20and%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20on%20ethical%20and%20safe%20AI%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wanted%20to%20write%20this%20book%20now%20to%20invite%20more%20people%20into%20the%20conversation%20so%20it's%20not%20just%20that%20you%20have%20to%20be%20in%20the%20tech%20industry.%20You%20certainly%20don't%20need%20a%20Ph.D.%20from%20MIT%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20conversation%2C%26quot%3B%20Buolamwini%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20these%20technologies%20are%20shaping%20everybody's%20life%20in%20many%20important%20ways%2C%20I%20wanted%20a%20book%20that%20was%20an%20invitation%20to%20say%2C%20'You're%20part%20of%20the%20conversation%20too%2C%20here%20is%20the%20context%2C%20but%20most%20importantly%2C%20here's%20what%20it%20means%20to%20you%2C'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuolamwini's%20curiosities%20were%20nurtured%20first%20at%20Georgia%20Tech%2C%20and%20she%20later%20journeyed%20through%20the%20gilded%20halls%20of%20MIT%2C%20where%20she%20earned%20her%20Ph.D.%20Her%20experiences%20as%20a%20student%20defined%20her%20discovery%20of%20what%20she%20calls%20the%20coded%20gaze%3A%20%26quot%3Bthe%20ways%20in%20which%20the%20priorities%2C%20preferences%2C%20and%20prejudices%20of%20those%20who%20have%20the%20power%20to%20shape%20technology%20can%20propagate%20harm%2C%20such%20as%20discrimination%20and%20erasure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20popular%20technologies%20are%20built%20with%20and%20perpetuate%20this%20exclusionary%20gaze%2C%20leading%20to%20detrimental%20consequences.%20Buolamwini%20especially%20documents%20the%20coded%20gaze%20applied%20to%20facial-recognition%20AI%20technologies%2C%20which%20serve%20as%20the%20subject%20for%20much%20of%20Buolamwini's%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20varying%20places%20in%20the%20book%2C%20I%20relived%20my%20excitement%20and%20eventual%20frustration%20as%20a%20young%20tech%20reporter%20covering%20the%20harm%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fin-every-reported-false-arrests-based-on-facial-recognition-that-person-has-been-black-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efacial%20recognition%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20wreaked%20on%20communities%20that%20looked%20like%20mine%20and%20were%20uncomfortably%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fmonicamelton%2F2019%2F07%2F23%2Fhud-bill-blocking-facial-recognition-wont-stop-landlords-plans-to-install-in-majority-black-building%2F%3Fsh%3D27636bbd24f8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eclose%20to%20home%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuolamwini%20also%20tells%20the%20story%20of%20a%20Brooklyn%20apartment%20complex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%2C%2090%25%20of%20tenants%20were%20people%20of%20color%2C%20mostly%20women%20and%20older%20adults%20%E2%80%94%20all%20groups%20that%20facial%20recognition%20has%20been%20scientifically%20proven%20to%20be%20less%20accurate%20on.%20When%20the%20building%20owner%20sought%20to%20use%20facial%20recognition%20as%20a%20means%20for%20tenants%20to%20access%20their%20homes%2C%20it%20was%20met%20with%20strong%20opposition%2C%20and%20Buolamwini%20wrote%20an%20amicus%20letter%20of%20support%20for%20their%20cause.%20The%20tenants%20eventually%20succeeded%20in%20fighting%20this%20encroachment%20on%20their%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20book's%20more%20personal%20and%20vulnerable%20anecdotes%2C%20we%20see%20the%20nexus%20of%20Buolamwini's%20lived%20experience%2C%20expertise%2C%20and%20activism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20early%20in%20her%20childhood%2C%20when%20she%20was%20misgendered%20and%20when%20other%20kids%20breathed%20a%20sigh%20of%20relief%20for%20not%20having%20skin%20as%20dark%20as%20hers%2C%20to%20a%20guard%20reaching%20for%20a%20gun%20at%20the%20sight%20of%20her%20at%20Davos%2C%20to%20the%20choice%20of%20a%20news%20network%20to%20feature%20a%20white%20male%20AI%20expert%20over%20her%20for%20a%20television%20segment%2C%20readers%20can%20feel%20the%20misogynoir%20that%20has%20cast%20a%20shadow%20on%20Buolamwini's%20life%20and%20achievements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20a%20guard%20reached%20for%20a%20gun%20as%20a%20friend%20tried%20to%20drop%20me%20off%20at%20a%20hotel%20for%20designated%20badge%20holders%2C%20I%20was%20reminded%20that%20my%20inclusion%20in%20certain%20spaces%20was%20the%20exception%20to%20overall%20exclusion%2C%26quot%3B%20Buolamwini%20writes%20of%20her%20experience%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feveryone-talking-about-ai-plenty-clearly-dont-understand-davos-wef-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20Economic%20Forum%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20through%20the%20exceptional%20quality%20of%20Buolamwini's%20life%20and%20research%2C%20her%20story%20becomes%20all%20the%20more%20human.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%20in%20the%20book%2C%20I%20was%20moved%20to%20tears%20by%20the%20story%20of%20Buolamwini%20writing%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Olympic%20gold%20medalist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsimone-biles-surprise-return-elite-gymnastics-competition-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESimone%20Biles%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20she%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsimone-biles-fires-back-at-criticism-her-tokyo-olympics-performance-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewithdrew%20from%20events%20at%20the%202020%20Olympic%20Games%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20letter%2C%20Buolamwini%20marveled%20at%20Biles'%20ability%20to%20%26quot%3Bput%20herself%20above%20the%20weight%20of%20gold.%26quot%3B%20Her%20actions%20may%20have%20been%20an%20even%20harder%20feat%20as%20a%20Black%20woman%20who's%20often%20praised%20for%20her%20ability%20to%20endure%20rather%20than%20care%20for%20herself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20one%20of%20one%20or%20one%20of%20few%2C%20there's%20this%20extra%20pressure%20we%20put%20on%20ourselves%20because%20of%20the%20level%20of%20scrutiny%20we%20know%20people%20in%20our%20position%20get%2C%26quot%3B%20Buolamwini%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20already%20internally%20a%20perfectionist%20and%20ext