0of%20its%20net%20profit%20in%20Q3%20to%20Rs%2017.5%20crore%20versus%20an%20year%20ago%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fstock-market-live-updates-on-feb-7-nse-bse-sensex-nifty-q3-result-todays-market-updates-124020700084_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fstock-market-live-updates-on-feb-7-nse-bse-sensex-nifty-q3-result-todays-market-updates-124020700084_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fstock-market-live-updates-on-feb-7-nse-bse-sensex-nifty-q3-result-todays-market-updates-124020700084_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20Constitution%20Bench%20Asks%20Why%20Advanced%20Sub-Castes%20Can't%20Be%20Excluded%20from%20Quotas%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20seven-judge%20Constitution%20Bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20asked%20why%20those%20sub-castes%20among%20the%20backward%20classes%20which%20are%20well%20off%20should%20not%20be%20excluded%20from%20reservation%20lists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20is%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud.%20It%20is%20examining%20the%20matter%20of%20whether%20state%20governments%20can%20identify%20and%20sub-classify%20groups%20within%20the%20Scheduled%20Caste%20category%2C%20with%20an%20eye%20on%20who%20deserves%20more.%20The%20matter%20was%20referred%20to%20this%20bench%20by%20a%20five-judge%20bench%20in%202020%2C%20when%20it%20held%20that%20a%20coordinate%20bench%E2%80%99s%20judgement%20on%20sub-classification%20not%20being%20permissible%20needed%20to%20be%20reconsidered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Vikram%20Nath%2C%20on%20the%20bench%2C%20asked%20on%20February%206%20as%20to%20why%20affluent%20sub-castes%20should%20not%20be%20made%20to%20compete%20with%20the%20General%20category.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fsc-queries-if-affluent-sub-castes-should-exit-reservation-list-to-make-more-room-for-the-weakest-in-the-category%2Farticle67817989.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhy%20should%20there%20be%20no%20exclusion%20%5Bfrom%20the%20reservation%20list%5D%3F%20Some%20of%20these%20sub-castes%20have%20done%20better%20and%20gone%20forward.%20They%20should%20come%20out%20of%20reservation%20and%20compete%20with%20the%20general%20category%E2%80%A6Why%20stay%20there%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Nath%20favoured%20advanced%20sub-castes%20ceding%20ground%20to%20more%20backward%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20remaining%20sub-castes%20who%20are%20still%20backward%2C%20let%20them%20have%20reservation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20also%20comprises%20Justices%20B.R.%20Gavai%2C%20Bela%20M.%20Trivedi%2C%20Pankaj%20Mithal%2C%20Manoj%20Misra%20and%20Satish%20Chandra%20Sharma.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Justice%20Gavai%20spoke%20on%20some%20families%20getting%20reservation%20benefits%20as%20a%20result%20of%20people%20entering%20into%20the%20public%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COnce%20a%20person%20gets%20into%20IPS%20or%20IAS%2C%20his%20children%20do%20not%20suffer%20from%20the%20disadvantages%20of%20others%20from%20his%20group%20who%20live%20in%20a%20village%E2%80%A6%20Yet%20his%20family%20will%20get%20the%20benefits%20of%20reservation%20for%20generations%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Gavai%20also%20said%20that%20it%20is%20upto%20the%20parliament%20to%20decide%20whether%20such%20a%20group%20can%20be%20kept%20out%20of%20the%20reservation%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsubclassification-necessary-to-uplift-most-backward-among-scheduled-castes-state-of-punjab-tells-supreme-court-day-1-248735%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20arguments%20were%20opened%20by%20Gurminder%20Singh%2C%20the%20Advocate%20General%20of%20Punjab%20who%20said%20that%20reservation%20cannot%20be%20seen%20as%20an%20act%20of%20benevolence.%20He%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%20Reservation%20is%20no%20benevolence%2C%20is%20not%20an%20act%20of%20benevolence%20by%20the%20entitled%20to%20the%20needy%20at%20all.%20If%20at%20all%20it%20is%2C%20it%20is%20the%20compensation%20for%20centuries%20of%20oppression%20of%20the%20needy%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%20highlighted%20the%20%E2%80%98heredity%20of%20caste%E2%80%99%20as%20an%20issue%20and%20spoke%20of%20caste-based%20occupations%20that%20offer%20few%20escape%20routes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECJI%20Chandrachud%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20verbally%20observed%20the%20underlining%20nuance%20of%20equity%20seen%20in%20the%20light%20of%20exclusive%2C%20according%20to%20LiveLaw%2C%20noting%20that%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20same%20exclusion%20that%20applies%20to%20reservation%20per%20se%20when%20courses%20are%20reserved%20for%20backward%20communities%2C%20there%20is%20necessarily%20an%20exclusion%20of%20the%20forward%20community%20in%20competing%20for%20those%20courses%2C%20yet%20our%20constitutional%20jurisprudence%20permits%20it.%20Why%2C%20because%20we%20treat%20equality%20as%20a%20substantive%20equality%2C%20not%20formal%20equality%20therefore%E2%80%A6.%20the%20same%20applies%20for%20the%20reservation%20of%20the%20backward%20community%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707285608000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthew