A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbhopal%2Fvarsity-act-amendment-v-cs-will-be-called-kul-gurus-now%2Farticleshow%2F107473903.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Uttarakhand%20Set%20to%20Pass%20UCC%3A%20Jail%20Time%20for%20Unregistered%20Live-in%20Relationship%3B%20Exemption%20for%20Tribals%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F07084315%2FScreenshot-2024-02-07-at-8.42.35-AM.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20With%20slogans%20of%20%E2%80%98Jai%20Shri%20Ram%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Vande%20Mataram%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Bharat%20Mata%20ki%20Jai%E2%80%99%20reverberating%20in%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party-dominated%20assembly%2C%20the%20Uttarakhand%20government%20on%20February%206%20tabled%20a%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20(UCC)%20Bill%20in%20the%20state%20assembly.%20A%20part%20of%20this%20Bill%20mandates%20compulsory%20registration%20of%20live-in%20relationships%20and%20punishment%20of%20three%20to%20six%20months%20in%20jail%20for%20failing%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20passed%2C%20Uttarakhand%20would%20become%20the%20first%20state%20in%20the%20country%20to%20implement%20a%20UCC%2C%20which%20has%20been%20a%20long-standing%20election%20agenda%20of%20the%20saffron%20party.%20The%20Opposition%20Congress%20accused%20the%20ruling%20BJP%20led%20by%20chief%20minister%20Pushkar%20Singh%20Dhami%20of%20introducing%20the%20Bill%20in%20the%20assembly%20without%20giving%20its%20MLAs%20time%20to%20study%20or%20review%20the%20provisions%2C%20and%20said%20it%20wanted%20to%20pass%20the%20law%20without%20debate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20bans%20bigamy%20or%20polygamy%3B%20regulates%20live-in%20relationships%20including%20setting%20up%20rules%20for%20their%20compulsory%20registration%20and%20punitive%20measures%20for%20failing%20to%20do%20so%3B%20standardises%20the%20process%20of%20divorce%20for%20both%20men%20and%20women%3B%20lays%20out%20procedure%20for%20compulsory%20registration%20of%20marriages%20and%20prohibits%20marriages%20and%20live-in%20relationships%20between%20those%20who%20fall%20within%20degrees%20of%20prohibited%20relationships%20such%20as%20close%20family%20members%20and%20relatives%3B%20and%20eliminates%20the%20distinction%20between%20legitimate%20and%20illegitimate%20children%20and%20treats%20adopted%20child%20on%20an%20equal%20footing%20as%20a%20biological%20child%20and%20provides%20equal%20inheritance%20rights%20for%20men%20and%20women.%20The%20Bill%20will%20not%20be%20applicable%20to%20members%20of%20the%20Scheduled%20Tribes%2C%20who%20are%20less%20than%203%25%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDhami%20described%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Chistoric%20moment%E2%80%9D%20and%20said%20that%20his%20government%20had%20introduced%20the%20Bill%20in%20the%20assembly%20taking%20along%20all%20sections%20of%20the%20society.%20%E2%80%9CThat%20historic%20moment%20is%20near%20for%20Devbhoomi%20when%20Uttarakhand%20will%20become%20a%20strong%20pillar%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20vision%20of%20%E2%80%98Ek%20Bharat%2C%20Shresth%20Bharat%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Dhami.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMandatory%20registration%20of%20live-in%20relationships%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20key%20highlight%20of%20The%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20of%20Uttarakhand%2C%202024%20is%20that%20it%20mandates%20the%20obligatory%20registration%20of%20live-in%20relationships.%20Even%20those%20residents%20of%20Uttarakhand%20who%20are%20in%20a%20live-in%20relationship%20outside%20the%20state%20must%20submit%20a%20statement%20to%20the%20registrar%20of%20the%20state.%20Those%20in%20a%20live-in%20relationship%2C%20or%20intending%20to%20get%20into%20one%2C%20will%20need%20to%20submit%20a%20statement%20of%20live-in%20relationship%20to%20the%20registrar%20who%20will%20carry%20out%20an%20inquiry%20which%20might%20include%20the%20persons%20or%20couple%20to%20provide%20additional%20information%20or%20evidence%20or%20be%20summoned%20for%20verification.%20After%20conducting%20the%20inquiry%2C%20the%20registrar%20shall%20within%2030%20days%20of%20the%20receipt%20of%20the%20statement%20of%20live-in%20either%20register%20the%20relationship%20and%20issue%20a%20certificate%20or%20refuse%20to%20register%20the%20statement.%20The%20partners%20will%20be%20informed%20about%20the%20denial%20of%20registration%20in%20writing.%20The%20Bill%20mandates%20that%20the%20registrar%20has%20to%20forward%20a%20statement%20of%20the%20live-in%20relationship%20to%20the%20in-charge%20of%20the%20local%20police%20station%20for%20record%20and%2C%20in%20case%20either%20of%20the%20partners%20is%20less%20than%2021%20years%20of%20age%2C%20also%20inform%20the%20parents%20or%20guardians%20of%20such%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22The%20Things%20We%20Need%20to%20Do%20Before%20We%20Speak%20of%20the%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fucc-tm-krishna-love-jihad-rights%5C%22%3EThe%20Things%20We%20Need%20to%20Do%20Before%20We%20Speak%20of%20the%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20says%20that%20whoever%20stays%20in%20a%20live-in%20relationship%20for%20more%20than%20one%20month%20without%20submitting%20the%20statement%20of%20such%20a%20relationship%20shall%20be%20punished%20on%20conviction%20by%20a%20judicial%20magistrate%20with%20imprisonment%20for%20a%20term%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20three%20months%20or%20with%20fine%20not%20exceeding%20Rs%2010%2C000%20or%20both.%20If%20the%20individuals%20submit%20false%20information%20or%20withholds%20information%20during%20registration%2C%20they%20would%20also%20face%20a%20jail%20term%20of%20three%20months%20and%20an%20ever%20bigger%20fine%20of%20Rs%2025%2C000.%20If%20any%20of%20the%20partners%20fails%20to%20submit%20the%20statement%20of%20live-in%20relationship%20on%20being%20required%20by%20a%20notice%2C%20they%20shall%20face%20a%20jail%20term%20of%20six%20months%20and%20Rs%2025%2C000%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UCC%20Bill%20also%20declares%20that%20a%20child%20of%20a%20live-in%20relationship%20shall%20also%20be%20a%20legitimate%20child%20of%20the%20couple%20and%20mandates%20that%20if%20a%20woman%20gets%20deserted%20by%20her%20live-in%20partner%2C%20she%20shall%20be%20entitled%20to%20claim%20maintenance%20from%20her%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERules%20on%20marriage%20and%20divorce%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20five-member%20committee%20of%20experts%20under%20retired%20judge%20Ranjana%20Prakash%20Desai%2C%20formed%20by%20the%20state%20government%20as%20part%20of%20its%20election%20promise%2C%20had%20last%20week%20submitted%20its%20report%20on%20the%20UCC%20to%20Dhami.%20The%20committee%20was%20to%20examine%20the%20relevant%20laws%20regulating%20personal%20civil%20matters%20of%20residents%20of%20the%20state%20and%20to%20prepare%20a%20draft%20law%20or%20suggest%20changes%20in%20existing%20laws%20on%20marriage%2C%20divorce%2C%20property%20rights%2C%20succession%2C%20inheritance%2C%20adoption%2C%20maintenance%2C%20custody%20and%20guardianship.%20The%20committee%20was%20also%20tasked%20with%20preparing%20a%20report%20on%20implementing%20a%20UCC%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UCC%20Bill%20draft%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20state%20assembly%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20two%20days%20after%20the%20cabinet%20gave%20a%20nod%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20makes%20compulsory%20the%20registration%20of%20marriage%20solemnised%20and%20contracted%20after%20the%20commencement%20of%20the%20UCC.%20It%20prohibits%20polygamy%20by%20stipulating%20that%20a%20person%20entering%20into%20a%20marriage%20should%20not%20have%20a%20living%20spouse%20and%20should%20be%20at%20least%2018%20(women)%20and%2021%20(men)%20years%20of%20age.%20Interestingly%2C%20it%20says%20that%20marriages%20may%20be%20solemnised%20or%20contracted%20between%20a%20man%20and%20a%20woman%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20religious%20beliefs%2C%20practices%2C%20customary%20rites%20and%20ceremonies%20including%20but%20not%20limited%20to%20%E2%80%9CSaptapadi%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CAshirvad%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CNikah%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CHoly%20Union%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CAnand%20Karaj%E2%80%9D%20under%20The%20Anand%20Marriage%20Act%201909%20as%20well%20as%20under%2C%20but%20not%20limited%20to%2C%20The%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201954%20and%20Arya%20Marriage%20Validation%20Act%2C%201937.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20also%20lays%20out%20a%20common%20procedure%20for%20divorce.%20Marriage%2C%20either%20before%20or%20after%20UCC%2C%20can%20be%20dissolved%20by%20either%20partner%20(through%20petition)%20on%20several%20grounds%20including%20cruelty%2C%20adultery%2C%20desertion%20for%20two%20years%20and%20conversion%20of%20religion.%20A%20wife%20may%20also%20present%20a%20petition%20to%20the%20court%20for%20the%20dissolution%20of%20marriage%20by%20a%20decree%20of%20divorce%20on%20the%20additional%20ground%20that%20the%20husband%20has%2C%20since%20the%20solemnisation%20or%20contracting%20of%20the%20marriage%2C%20been%20guilty%20of%20rape%20or%20any%20other%20kind%20of%20unnatural%20sexual%20offence%20or%20that%20the%20husband%20had%20more%20than%20one%20wife%20from%20marriages%20solemnised%20before%20the%20commencement%20of%20the%20UCC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOpposition%20to%20the%20Bill%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPremchand%20Aggarwal%2C%20cabinet%20minister%2C%20while%20introducing%20the%20UCC%2C%20said%20a%20policy%20of%20%E2%80%9Cappeasement%E2%80%9D%20had%20prevented%20previous%20governments%20from%20bringing%20in%20such%20a%20law.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20UCC%20gives%20uniform%20rights%20to%20women%20of%20all%20castes%20and%20religions%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Aggarwal%20in%20the%20assembly%20while%20seated%20next%20to%20Dhami.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAggarwal%20also%20tried%20to%20counter%20charges%20by%20the%20Opposition%20about%20the%20intent%20of%20the%20BJP%20behind%20a%20UCC%2C%20saying%20that%20even%20Muslim%20countries%20such%20as%20Egypt%2C%20Turkey%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20Malaysia%2C%20Sudan%2C%20Pakistan%20and%20Indonesia%20had%20a%20uniform%20civil%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22The%20Social%20and%20Economic%20Dangers%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98Mother%20of%20Democracy%E2%80%99%20if%20a%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20Is%20Implemented%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fthe-social-and-economic-dangers-to-the-mother-of-democracy-if-a-uniform-civil-code-is-implemented%5C%22%3EThe%20Social%20and%20Economic%20Dangers%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98Mother%20of%20Democracy%E2%80%99%20if%20a%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20Is%20Implemented%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20said%20its%20MLAs%20were%20not%20given%20any%20time%20to%20prepare%20for%20a%20discussion%20on%20the%20Bill%20and%20were%20not%20kept%20in%20the%20loop%20on%20the%20content%20of%20the%20expert%20committee%20report.%20Congress%20MLA%20and%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20Yashpal%20Arya%20said%20before%20introducing%20the%20Bill%2C%20the%20government%20should%20have%20presented%20the%20expert%20committee%20report%20for%20discussion.%20Arya%20accused%20the%20government%20of%20depriving%20Opposition%20MLAs%20of%20their%20right%20to%20ask%20questions%20after%20the%20Question%20Hour%20was%20waived%20off%20for%20this%20session.%20Arya%20suggested%20that%20the%20Bill%20be%20sent%20to%20a%20select%20committee%20to%20examine%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20are%20suppressing%20the%20voice%20of%20the%20MLAs%20on%20the%20strength%20of%20their%20numbers.%20We%20didn%E2%80%99t%20even%20get%20time%20to%20review%20the%20report%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Arya%2C%20who%20further%20accused%20the%20ruling%20party%20of%20undermining%20the%20rules%20of%20the%20assembly%20and%20setting%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnew%20precedent%E2%80%9D%20by%20ignoring%20constitutional%20traditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20is%20yet%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20specific%20provisions%20of%20the%20UCC%20Bill.%20Arya%2C%20however%2C%20said%20he%20was%20not%20against%20the%20UCC.%20Former%20chief%20minister%20Harish%20Rawat%2C%20talking%20to%20a%20news%20agency%2C%20asked%20if%20the%20Union%20government%20would%20allow%20others%20states%20too%20to%20bring%20in%20similar%20laws%2C%20even%20as%20it%20has%20promised%20to%20bring%20in%20a%20UCC%20at%20the%20national%20level.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20a%20state%20government%20brings%20in%20a%20law%20for%20the%20ruling%20class%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20UCC%20to%20intervene%20in%20the%20personal%20tradition%20of%20another%20community%20for%20vote%20bank%20politics%2C%20won%E2%80%99t%20there%20be%20disharmony%20in%20the%20state%3F%E2%80%9D%20Rawat%20asked.%20He%20took%20the%20example%20of%20the%20ethnic%20conflict%20in%20Manipur%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJamiat%20Ulama-i-Hind%20president%20Maulana%20Arshad%20Madani%20said%20he%20could%20not%20accept%20any%20law%20that%20was%20against%20the%20Shariah%20and%20said%20that%20the%20UCC%20was%20in%20conflict%20with%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20given%20to%20citizens.%20Commenting%20on%20the%20exclusion%20of%20STs%20from%20the%20UCC%2C%20under%20Sub-Section%20342%20of%20Chapter%2025%20of%20Article%20366%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%20Madani%20asked%20that%20if%20tribals%20can%20be%20exempted%20from%20the%20law%20then%20%E2%80%9Cwhy%20religious%20freedom%20cannot%20be%20given%20to%20us%20under%20Sections%2024%20and%2026%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20recognising%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20citizens.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20legal%20team%20of%20the%20JUH%20will%20review%20the%20legal%20aspects%20of%20the%20Bill%20and%20take%20a%20decision%20on%20legal%20action%2C%20said%20Madani.%20%E2%80%9CReligious%20freedom%20is%20guaranteed%3B%20thus%2C%20the%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20negates%20fundamental%20rights.%20If%20it%20is%20a%20uniform%20civil%20code%20then%20why%20this%20distinction%20between%20citizens%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707275883000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F07084315%2FScreenshot-2024-02-07-at-8.42.35-AM.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Futtarakhand-tables-ucc-jail-time-for-unregistered-live-in-relationship-exemption-for-tribals%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Congress%20has%20alleged%20that%20its%20MLAs%20were%20not%20given%20enough%20time%20to%20read%20and%20respond%20to%20the%20Bill.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Futtarakhand-tables-ucc-jail-time-for-unregistered-live-in-relationship-exemption-for-tribals%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bengal%3A%20English-medium%20education%20at%2014%20more%20madrasas%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707275653000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107482099%2Cimgsize-3400.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fkolkata%2Feng-medium-education-at-14-more-madrasas%2Farticleshow%2F107473697.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TNN%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fkolkata%2Feng-medium-education-at-14-more-madrasas%2Farticleshow%2F107473697.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22BJP%20Has%20Made%20the%20Bharat%20Ratna%20an%20Electoral%20Tool%20%E2%80%93%20and%20Nothing%20Else%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F07081636%2Ffe481c05-1d3b-4606-92b8-bc40bac09c3a.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Narendra%20Modi%20regime%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fl-k-advani-from-rath-yatra-to-bharat-ratna%5C%22%3Edecision%20to%20confer%20the%20Bharat%20Ratna%20on%20L.K.%20Advani%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20Hindutva%20icon%2C%20a%20few%20weeks%20after%20it%20announced%20the%20same%20honour%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fkarpoori-thakur-bharat-ratna%5C%22%3Eposthumously%20on%20Karpoori%20Thakur%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20his%20stellar%20role%20in%20reserving%20jobs%20for%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%20(OBCs)%20in%20Bihar%20in%201977%20smacks%20of%20political%20motives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECocktail%20of%20Mandal%20and%20Kamandal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdvani%E2%80%99s%20Rath%20Yatra%20advocating%20for%20a%20Ram%20temple%20exactly%20where%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20stood%20aimed%20at%20countering%20the%20V.P.%20Singh%20government%E2%80%99s%20historic%20implementation%20of%20the%20Mandal%20Commission%20report%2C%20recommending%2027%25%20reservation%20for%20OBCs%20in%20government%20jobs.%20In%20popular%20perception%2C%20this%20Yatra%20represented%20Kamandal%2C%20associated%20with%20Hindutva%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20Mandal%20representing%20affirmative%20action.%20The%20BJP%20under%20Advani%20looked%20at%20reserving%20jobs%20for%20OBCs%20as%20dividing%20Hindus%20based%20on%20caste%3B%20it%20entertained%20the%20hope%20that%20the%20Yatra%20would%20unite%20Hindus%20on%20a%20Hindutva%20plank.%20It%20was%20also%20an%20attempt%20to%20unleash%20forces%20for%20cultural%20nationalism%20as%20opposed%20to%20the%20constitutional%20vision%20of%20a%20secular%20India%20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20awarding%20Advani%20and%20Karpoori%20Thakur%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20in%20the%20words%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20founding%20editor%20M.K.%20Venu%2C%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cperfect%20cocktail%20of%20Mandal%20and%20Kamandal%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20a%20shrewd%20political%20move%20ahead%20of%20the%202024%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBJP%E2%80%99s%20Maharashtra%20manifesto%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20isn%E2%80%99t%20the%20first%20time%20a%20Bharat%20Ratna%20award%20has%20been%20seen%20in%20this%20way.%20In%201988%2C%20when%20Prime%20Minister%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20posthumously%20bestowed%20the%20Bharat%20Ratna%20on%20the%20late%20chief%20minister%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%20M.G.%20Ramachandran%2C%20it%20was%20widely%20viewed%20in%20the%20media%20as%20an%20attempt%20to%20enhance%20the%20Congress%20party%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20fortunes%20in%20the%201989%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20no%20political%20party%20in%20India%20has%20politicised%20the%20Bharat%20Ratna%20like%20the%20BJP%20has.%20In%202019%2C%20in%20its%20manifesto%20before%20the%20Maharashtra%20assembly%20elections%2C%20it%20p%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjps-maharashtra-unit-wants-bharat-ratna-for-savarkar%5C%22%3Eromised%20to%20confer%20a%20Bharat%20Ratna%20on%20V.D.%20Savarkar%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20preceded%20Mohammed%20Ali%20Jinnah%20in%20saying%20that%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%20constituted%20two%20separate%20nations%2C%20and%20none%20other%20than%20Sardar%20Vallabhbhai%20Patel%20wrote%20that%20a%20fanatical%20wing%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%20led%20by%20Savarkar%20had%20conspired%20to%20kill%20Mahatma%20Gandhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20K.R.%20Narayanan%20had%20rejected%20the%20Bharat%20Ratna%20for%20Savarkar%20in%202001%2C%20after%20Prime%20Minister%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20suggested%20his%20name.%20Vajapyee%20agreed%20to%20Narayanan%E2%80%99s%20proposal%20in%202000%20for%20the%20Bharat%20Ratna%20for%20%3Cem%3Eshehnai%3C%2Fem%3E%20maestro%20Bismillah%20Khan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Why%20Bharat%20Ratnas%20to%20Karpoori%20and%20Advani%20Reveal%20That%20Mandal%20and%20Kamandal%20Are%20Polls%20Apart%C2%A0%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbharat-ratna-karpoori-thakur-advani-mandal-kamandal%5C%22%3EWhy%20Bharat%20Ratnas%20to%20Karpoori%20and%20Advani%20Reveal%20That%20Mandal%20and%20Kamandal%20Are%20Polls%20Apart%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20president%20and%20prime%20minister%20take%20the%20decision%20to%20confer%20a%20Bharat%20Ratna.%20Narayanan%20proposed%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20name%20and%20the%20prime%20minister%20agreed%2C%20while%20in%20turn%20proposing%20the%20name%20of%20Savarkar.%20Narayanan%20sat%20over%20the%20proposal%20for%20several%20months.%20When%20on%20the%20occasion%20of%20Vajpayee%E2%80%99s%20birth%20anniversary%20on%20December%2025%2C%202001%20Narayanan%20visited%20him%20to%20convey%20his%20greetings%2C%20Vajpayee%20told%20that%20he%20was%20withdrawing%20his%20proposal%20for%20Savarkar%20as%20he%20felt%20that%20it%20was%20pending%20with%20the%20president%20for%20a%20long%20time%20and%20so%20he%20was%20not%20inclined%20to%20approve%20it.%20He%20requested%20Narayanan%20to%20accordingly%20dispose%20of%20the%20file%2C%20recording%20approval%20for%20the%20Bharat%20Ratna%20for%20Khan.%20It%20is%20rather%20strange%20that%2020%20years%20after%20that%20incident%2C%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20Bharat%20Ratna%20for%20Savarkar%20was%20used%20as%20bait%20for%20an%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%20went%20against%20Karpoori%20Thakur%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20will%20never%20be%20forgotten%20that%20when%20Karpoori%20Thakur%20as%20chief%20minister%20of%20Bihar%20introduced%2026%25%20reservation%20for%20OBCs%20and%20marginalised%20sections%20in%20government%20jobs%20in%201978%2C%20it%20was%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%20(the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20predecessor)%20which%20opposed%20it%20and%20caused%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20state%20government.%20It%20also%20used%20abusive%20language%20against%20Thakur%20and%20RSS%20cadres%20%E2%80%93%20most%20hailing%20from%20the%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20castes%20%E2%80%93%20did%20not%20spare%20even%20his%20mother.%20They%20coined%20a%20highly%20offensive%20slogan%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EYe%20reservation%20kahan%20se%20aai%2C%20Karpoori%20ke%20mai%20biyayi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Where%20did%20this%20reservation%20come%20from%3F%20Karpoori%E2%80%99s%20mother%20has%20birthed%20it).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20announcing%20the%20Bharat%20Ratna%20decision%2C%20Modi%20said%20that%20he%20used%20to%20hear%20about%20Thakur%E2%80%99s%20pioneering%20role%20on%20social%20justice%20from%20the%20then%20Jan%20Sangh%20leader%20of%20Bihar%2C%20Kailashpati%20Mishra.%20What%20he%20said%20lacked%20conviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20Modi%20government%20was%20so%20keen%20to%20recognise%20leaders%20of%20the%20social%20justice%20movement%2C%20it%20should%20have%20long%20back%20honoured%20Tamil%20Nadu%E2%80%99s%20legendary%20leader%20K.%20Karunanidhi.%20He%20was%20an%20exemplary%20product%20of%20the%20Dravidian%20movement%20which%20pioneered%20the%20cause%20of%20social%20justice%20in%20India%20from%20the%201920s.%20An%20extraordinary%20leader%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20public%20life%2C%20he%20as%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%20during%201969%20and%201971%20preceded%20Karpoori%20Thakur%20in%20taking%20numerous%20measures%20including%20increasing%20the%20quota%20for%20OBCs%20in%20his%20state%20from%2025%25%20to%2031%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20celebrating%20Thakur%20and%20ignoring%20Karunanidhi%2C%20the%20Modi%20regime%20has%20proved%20it%20is%20more%20interested%20in%20pursuing%20its%20electoral%20prospects%20in%20the%20Hindi%20heartland%20of%20the%20north%2C%20where%20it%20is%20advantageously%20placed%2C%20than%20in%20the%20south.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20preposterous%20to%20determine%20the%20worth%20of%20a%20person%20based%20on%20electoral%20outcome.%20Yet%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20exactly%20what%20the%20BJP%20is%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ES.N.%20Sahu%20served%20as%20Officer%20on%20Special%20Duty%20to%20President%20of%20India%20K.R.%20Narayanan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707274811000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F07081636%2Ffe481c05-1d3b-4606-92b8-bc40bac09c3a.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-has-made-the-bharat-ratna-an-electoral-tool-and-nothing-else%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20was%20already%20visible%20in%202019%2C%20when%20it%20proposed%20the%20Bharat%20Ratna%20for%20V.D.%20Savarkar%20in%20its%20Maharashtra%20election%20manifesto.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-has-made-the-bharat-ratna-an-electoral-tool-and-nothing-else%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Cognizant%20Q4%20profit%20up%207%25%20at%20%24558%20mn%2C%202024%20revenue%20guidance%20at%20-2%25%20to%202%25%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707274714000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2022-05%2F05%2Ffull%2F1651741329-9269.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcognizant-q4-profit-up-7-at-558-mn-2024-revenue-guidance-at-2-to-2-124020700099_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20firm%2C%20based%20in%20Teaneck%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20reported%20a%207%20per%20cent%20increase%20in%20net%20profit%20at%20%24558%20million%20for%20the%20December%20quarter%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcognizant-q4-profit-up-7-at-558-mn-2024-revenue-guidance-at-2-to-2-124020700099_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcognizant-q4-profit-up-7-at-558-mn-2024-revenue-guidance-at-2-to-2-124020700099_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcognizant-q4-profit-up-7-at-558-mn-2024-revenue-guidance-at-2-to-2-124020700099_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22HDFC%20Bank%20accepts%20bids%20worth%20%2475