3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F27110211%2FScreenshot-2023-05-27-at-11.00.50-AM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20Tuesday%20(February%206)%20passed%20the%20Public%20Examinations%20(Prevention%20of%20Unfair%20Means)%20Bill%2C%202024%2C%20which%20seeks%20to%20prevent%20paper%20leaks%20and%20malpractices%20in%20government%20recruitment%20examinations%20and%20provides%20for%20punishment%2C%20including%20imprisonment%20of%20up%20to%20ten%20years%20and%20a%20fine%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%201%20crore.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20closing%20remarks%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20debate%2C%20which%20saw%20about%2015%20MPs%20participate%2C%20minister%20of%20state%20in%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Office%20Jitendra%20Singh%20said%20that%20the%20legislation%20%E2%80%9Cseeks%20to%20provide%20a%20level%20playing%20field%20and%20save%20the%20meritorious%20and%20deserving%20from%20the%20ordeal%20of%20being%20wronged%20by%20sinful%20operators%20of%20malpractices.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20need%20to%20bring%20in%20a%20separate%20legislation%2C%20Singh%20said%20that%20the%20need%20arose%20because%20the%20existing%20Bharatiya%20Nyay%20Sanhita%20(BNS)%20does%20not%20define%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20tried%20to%20define%20unfair%20means%20for%20the%20conduct%20of%20examinations%20to%20the%20best%20of%20our%20abilities.%20If%20the%20magnitude%20of%20the%20crime%20goes%20beyond%2C%20it%20will%20go%20into%20the%20domain%20of%20the%20BNS%20or%20the%20erstwhile%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bill%20comes%20as%20the%20issue%20of%20paper%20leaks%20in%20government%20recruitment%20examinations%20have%20dominated%20state%20polls%20as%20recently%20as%20the%20assembly%20elections%20in%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Rajasthan%20and%20Telangana%20in%20December%20last%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Rajasthan%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20had%20accused%20the%20then-Congress%20government%20of%20not%20acting%20on%20paper%20leaks%20and%20alleged%20that%20senior%20party%20functionaries%20were%20involved.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilarly%2C%20in%20Telangana%2C%20the%20Congress%20had%20also%20accused%20the%20then-BRS%20government%20of%20leaks%20in%20exams%20conducted%20by%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20public%20service%20commission.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexpress-exclusive%2Fthe-big-all-india-exam-leak-over-5-years-1-4-crore-job-seekers-in-15-states-bore-the-brunt-9145910%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Einvestigation%20by%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIndian%20Express%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ethere%20have%20been%2041%20documented%20instances%20of%20leaks%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years%20in%20recruitment%20exams%20across%2015%20states.%20These%20affected%20as%20many%20as%201.4%20crore%20applicants%20applying%20for%20a%20little%20over%201.04%20lakh%20posts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESingh%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmenace%E2%80%9D%20is%20being%20felt%20across%20the%20country%2C%20including%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20but%20claimed%20that%20since%20the%20government%20change%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20where%20the%20BJP%20ousted%20the%20Congress%20government%20on%20the%20back%20of%20its%20promise%20to%20plug%20paper%20leaks%2C%20such%20leaks%20have%20stopped%20since.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20the%20Bill%20states%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20public%20examinations%20under%20the%20Bill%20refer%20to%20examinations%20conducted%20by%20authorities%20specified%20under%20the%20Schedule%20to%20the%20Bill%20or%20notified%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20include%20the%20Union%20Public%20Service%20Commission%2C%20Staff%20Selection%20Commission%2C%20Railway%20Recruitment%20Board%2C%20National%20Testing%20Agency%2C%20Institute%20of%20Banking%20Personnel%20Selection%2C%20and%20Departments%20of%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20their%20attached%20offices%20for%20recruitment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20an%20analysis%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Fbilltrack%2Fthe-public-examinations-prevention-of-unfair-means-bill-2024%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPRS%20Legislative%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20Bill%20specifies%20unfair%20means%20in%20public%20examinations%20as%20including%20unauthorised%20access%20to%20or%20leakage%20of%20a%20question%20paper%20or%20answer%20key%2C%20assisting%20a%20candidate%20during%20a%20public%20examination%2C%20tampering%20with%20a%20computer%20network%20or%20resources%2C%20tampering%20with%20documents%20for%20the%20shortlisting%20or%20finalising%20of%20merit%20lists%20or%20ranks%2C%20and%20conducting%20a%20fake%20examination%2C%20issuing%20fake%20admit%20cards%20or%20offer%20letters%20to%20cheat%2C%20for%20monetary%20gain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20also%20prohibits%20disclosing%20exam-related%20confidential%20information%20before%20time%20and%20unauthorised%20people%20from%20entering%20exam%20centres%20to%20create%20disruptions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20offences%20will%20be%20punishable%20with%20imprisonment%20between%20three%20and%20five%20years%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20fine%20up%20to%20Rs%2010%20lakh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bill%20provides%20that%20an%20offence%20by%20a%20service%20provider%20(an%20organisation%20that%20provides%20computer%20resources%20or%20any%20other%20support%20to%20a%20public%20examination%20authority)%20will%20be%20punishable%20with%20a%20fine%20of%20up%20to%20one%20crore%20rupees.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20also%20provides%20that%20in%20cases%20of%20organised%20crime%20related%20to%20public%20examinations%2C%20punishment%20will%20include%20imprisonment%20between%20five%20and%2010%20years%2C%20and%20a%20fine%20of%20at%20least%20Rs%201%20crore.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20offences%20under%20the%20Bill%20will%20be%20cognisable%2C%20non-bailable%20and%20non-compoundable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Punishment%20itself%20a%20deterrent%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECongress%20MP%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%20said%20that%20the%20Bill%20has%20%E2%80%9Cpenal%20measures%20but%20does%20not%20include%20preventive%20measures%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20said%20that%20the%20Bill%20gives%20%E2%80%9Csignificant%20authority%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthus%20consolidating%20considerable%20control%20of%20investigation%20at%20%5Bits%5D%20hands%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20that%20it%20can%20easily%20be%20assumed%20that%20%E2%80%9Call%20kinds%20of%20opposition%20will%20be%20throttled%20with%20this%20kind%20of%20legislation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CPunishment%20itself%20is%20a%20deterrent%20and%20a%20preventive%20measure.%20This%20is%20the%20first%20step%20for%20prevention.%20If%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20take%20even%20this%20first%20step%2C%20we%20will%20not%20be%20doing%20anything%20at%20all%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Singh%20in%20his%20closing%20remarks%20referring%20to%20Choudhury%E2%80%99s%20concerns.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20denied%20that%20the%20legislation%20attempts%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccentralise%20the%20system%E2%80%9D%20in%20any%20form%20through%20the%20legislation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENationalist%20Congress%20Party%20MP%20Supriya%20Sule%2C%20while%20supporting%20the%20Bill%2C%20said%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20should%20clarify%20its%20plans%20to%20tackle%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdelay%20and%20cancellation%E2%80%9D%20of%20examinations%20and%20the%20enforcement%20of%20a%20timeline%20for%20conducting%20substitute%20exams.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20also%20cautioned%20against%20the%20criminal%20offences%20in%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20appreciate%20your%20intent.%20But%20let%E2%80%99s%20not%20criminalise%20everybody%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESingh%20in%20his%20closing%20remarks%20however%20said%20that%20no%20timeline%20could%20be%20set.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20any%20examination%20is%20cancelled%2C%20it%20should%20be%20conducted%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%20This%20suggestion%20should%20be%20well-taken%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Singh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20examinations%20are%20cancelled%2C%20it%20is%20done%20for%20various%20reasons%2C%20either%20for%20a%20CBI%20enquiry%20or%20any%20other%20investigative%20agency.%20So%20it%20might%20not%20be%20possible%20to%20set%20a%20timeline%2C%20but%20we%20will%20try%20to%20conduct%20it%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707239378000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F27110211%2FScreenshot-2023-05-27-at-11.00.50-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Flok-sabha-passes-public-examinations-bill%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Punishment%20itself%20is%20a%20deterrent%2C%E2%80%99%20said%20PMO%20minister%20of%20state%20Jitendra%20Singh%20amid%20concerns%20from%20opposition%20MPs%20that%20the%20Public%20Examinations%20(Prevention%20of%20Unfair%20Means)%20Bill%2C%202024%20does%20not%20look%20at%20the%20prevention%20of%20leaks.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2